Custom Output from `mzExacto()`

Source: R/standard_exacto.R
standard_exacto.Rd

A data set containing all of the output from `mzExacto(standard_spread, query_chemicals)` `mzExacto()`

standard_exacto

Format

## `standard_exacto` A data frame with 4 rows and 7 columns.

Compound

Column with Chemical Names

Mass

Column with Published Chemical Masses

RT

Column with Best Identified Retention Times

Best Match

Column with the Top Match Factors

Std_soln_00.D

Column with Component Areas for First Sample

Std_soln_07.D

Column with Component Areas for Second Sample

Std_soln_00a.D

Column with Component Areas for Third Sample
